'''Clive Revill''' ([[April 18]], [[1930s|1930]]<ref name="LEGO A-Wing Starfighter" /> &mdash; [[March 11]], [[2025]]<ref name="Death" />) was an actor from New Zealand who provided voice of [[Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Darth Sidious|Palpatine]] in the [[1980]] theatrical release of [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''The Empire Strikes Back'']]. [[Marjorie Eaton]] portrayed Palpatine physically. When the film was released on DVD in 2004, both Revill and Eaton were replaced by [[Ian McDiarmid]].<ref name="SWI49">{{InsiderCite|49|Clive Revill: Voice of the Emperor}}</ref>

